<capabilities>
The Scorpion is moderately effective against light armor units but falls short in speed and armor for a light tank. Its main weapon, the Deleon Autocannon, delivers marginal long-range damage but faces tracking issues at close range. The 20mm Gatling gun, though reliable, is less effective compared to the secondary armaments of similar class tanks. Additionally, the Scorpion is notorious for quality control issues, with many units experiencing various minor problems.
</capabilities>

<overview>
The Scorpion Light Tank, a product of the Quikscell Company, is known for its affordability, earning the nickname “Budget Tank.” Its low cost makes it a popular choice for buyers from economically challenged worlds. Field commanders often deploy the Scorpion in large numbers to offset its relative weaknesses compared to other vehicles.
</overview>

