<history>
Manufactured across the Inner Sphere since 2807, the Scorpion has been a staple in many armies, militias, and even among bandit groups. Notable in its history is its role in the "Scorpions Nest" battle on Santander V, where bandit king Helmar Valasek used Scorpions to inflict significant damage on invading Kurita forces. This battle highlighted the tank's potential when used in large numbers and in ambush tactics.<p>The Scorpion was a key asset for the Free Rasalhague Republic until the Ghost Bears' invasion. However, its limitations were starkly revealed during the ambush by the 603rd Tank Regiment against the First Kavalleri, where the Scorpion's inferiority to medium tanks was evident.</p>
<p>Variants of the Scorpion have been developed over the years, reflecting adaptations to different combat roles and environments. These include the LRM variant for long-range support, the SRM variant for increased firepower, the ML variant for scouting, the MRM and LAC variants for enhanced missile and light autocannon capabilities, and specialized models like the Minesweeper and Desert Scorpion for specific operational needs.</p>
</history>

